; ─── Blocker 1: unstable working tree ──────────────────────────

(blocker
  :id 1
  :severity "high"
  :summary "The shared worktree is being modified concurrently by 15+ other lanes; CLI stability oscillates minute-by-minute."
  :evidence (
    "src/sakuraEnv.js imports src/game-theory.js which is untracked / not-yet-committed."
    "src/reference-register.js imports { loadSchema, validateEntry } from src/reference-loader.js which does not export them on HEAD."
    "src/commercial.js calls installCardVerbs/installShoppeVerbs which are undefined in the shipped commercial.js."
    "src/sakuraEnv.js imports installWiredVerbsIP from src/wired-verbs-priya-i-p.js which is untracked."
    "Stashes from other lane agents (marcus-hold, marcus-hold2, marcus-hold3, hiroshi-wip, sora-everything) accumulate in git stash list."
    "./bin/sakura-scheme eval succeeds on some minutes, fails with ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND on others as concurrent files appear/disappear."
  )
  :impact "The no-lie rule requires REPL-verified examples via ./bin/sakura-scheme eval for every tier. When the CLI oscillates between working and broken based on which sibling lanes' files exist that instant, I cannot guarantee a verified commit."
  :ask "Coordinator: stabilize the worktree — either land the concurrent lanes' half-committed changes to green or roll them back — before per-verb Phase B commits from this lane. Alternatively, provide isolated worktrees per lane."
)

; ─── Blocker 2: keyword argument syntax not implemented in interp ──

(blocker
  :id 2
  :severity "medium"
  :summary "The reference documents motion/move-to, motion/pocket, motion/with-feel, motion/with-pace, etc. with :kw syntax that the interp cannot evaluate."
  :evidence (
    "docs/SAKURA-SCHEME-REFERENCE.slat:14834 documents (motion/move-to target x y :ms duration :curve easing-name)"
    "docs/SAKURA-SCHEME-REFERENCE.slat:14852 documents (motion/pocket :tolerance-ms tolerance :count n)"
    "docs/SAKURA-SCHEME-REFERENCE.slat:14870 documents (motion/with-feel tensor-id :articulation style)"
    "docs/SAKURA-SCHEME-REFERENCE.slat:14888 documents (motion/with-pace tensor-id :intensity level)"
    "./bin/sakura-scheme eval '(define (foo . args) args) (foo :a 1 :b 2)' → 'unbound symbol: :a'"
    "The interp treats :symbol as a variable lookup, not a self-evaluating keyword."
    "Quoted keywords work: ':a evaluates to symbol :a. But then examples must write (motion/pocket ':tolerance-ms 16 ':count 3) which the reference does not use."
  )
  :impact "Cannot write Phase B examples that match the documented signature without either (a) adding keyword self-eval to interp.js (touches other lanes) or (b) rewriting the reference signatures away from :kw form."
  :ask "Alfred / language design: decide between (a) add keyword self-eval to src/interp.js — :symbol evaluates to itself when its first char is ':'. Standard R7RS-ish extension. Or (b) rewrite the reference signatures to use positional-args-only. My preference is (a); it makes the reference internally consistent."
  :non-blocking-if "Ren accepts approach (a) or (b) and either is landed."
)

; ─── Blocker 3: description-vs-implementation semantic mismatch for grid flowers ─

(blocker
  :id 3
  :severity "low"
  :summary "The reference describes grid/flower-* verbs as reading/writing a _flowers Map that exists somewhere. That store doesn't exist in the codebase yet."
  :evidence (
    "grep -rn '_flowers' src/  → no hits."
    "Reference for grid/flower-spawn! says 'adds a new flower entry to the internal _flowers registry'."
    "Reference for grid/flower-list says 'queries the internal _flowers registry'."
    "No src/grid.js exists."
  )
  :impact "Wiring grid/* requires creating src/grid.js with a module-scoped _flowers Map, a pending-dots buffer, a pending-glows buffer, and a card-layout lookup. This is straightforward but not zero-work. It's the correct move; just needs to be in a fresh clean commit."
  :ask "None — I'll create src/grid.js in Phase B wave 2 once blockers 1+2 are cleared."
  :non-blocking-if "Blockers 1+2 clear."
)

